µJEDarkness falls into my eyes when I see the current state of my activities in the scene, what I thought that would never happen has happened sooner as I could ever imagine. I lost complete interest in the scene, her wonderful feelings.

Somewhere during July last year I wanted to take it a bit easier, some private things took my time and I wasn't able to write or even think about the scene. Perhaps it started even before July, many of my mails weren't answered by the people who should have answered them and no one took the time to explain to me what should have been explained. So I threw the towel into the ring for a while, not that I wanted to quit the scene and leave [S], no I needed some rest I think, but from rest came laziness and laziness means inactivity.

So I was quite inactive for a few months and waited for that little push into the right direction to get back the scene feeling that runs through my veins for so long now. But I kept waiting for that push, so long now that I wonder if there will be any push at all. Perhaps a punch, right into the stomach would get me out of my hibernation. And I guess there are some sceners that would love to punch me into the stomach, but what I meant is well meant punch.

It's now the end of October (2004) and not one of my close scene friends/contacts even wondered where I am, or how things are. Not even the ones I try to support the most. Hmm, not that I blame them for my inactivity, but isn't it strange that none took the time to send me a private email why I wasn't on the mail anymore or active in anyway. I don't blame certain sceners and am not mad, but now I know why many sceners decide to leave the scene, there isn't any form of brotherhood anymore to find within this scene. Or perhaps my mind is playing tricks on me, and it's all my own fault and I banned the scene out of my head.

I gave away my miggy and threw 300 of floppies filled with scene wares from the early scene until now into the trash. My wife was pretty happy though with that. I broke down the desk, which was on the attic and have now more room to store other useless stuff.

Recently this week I checked my mail once again and guess what, only spam. I check the [S] website, still lovely as usual. And I took a visit on Diskmag.de to see the latest news, and saw that nothing has changed. The scene is still the scene.

So you may say I left the scene, but I haven't forgotten it. Or: You may say the scene didn't leave me, but it has forgotten me.


